  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Until the power ends, freezing rain and sleet fall in a 20-foot-tall cylinder with a 40-foot radius centered on a point you choose within range. The area is heavily obscured, and exposed flames in the area are doused.</p><p>The ground in the area is covered with slick ice, making it difficult terrain. When a creature enters the power's area for the first time on a turn or starts its turn there, it must make a Dexterity saving throw. On a failed save, it falls Prone.</p><p>If a creature is concentrating in the power's area, the creature must make a successful Constitution saving throw against your power save DC or lose concentration.</p>",
